President Trump announced that the Defense Production Act will be invoked in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The act will allow the government to increase the production of medical supplies and equipment, such as ventilators, to combat the virus. The President also announced that FEMA is now activated in every region and that two hospital ships, the Mercy and the Comfort, will be deployed to help with the response efforts. Additionally, the President mentioned the progress being made in developing a vaccine and expanding testing capacity. He also addressed concerns about the virus being called the "Chinese virus," stating that it comes from China and is not racist to refer to it as such. The President emphasized the need for everyone to work together and follow guidelines to slow the spread of the virus.